column5: Have you ever gone to GOOGLE and typed in your own name, or even the name of a family member or friend to see what information pops up ??........give it a try.  My grandfather was born in England in 1896, so this morning, to see if anything would come up, I typed in his name and the town he was born in and the story that came up was about a man with the same name as my grandfather, who was executed in 1922 for murdering his own mother  So, either their talking about a different man, or I don't really exist   hmmmmmm.........
Apparently I played 20 games in the nfl. 1994 9 games for the LA Raiders and 1997 11 games for the New Orleans Saints.
Tried it once, apparently I was murdered in Alberta sometime in the 90's.  Decided at that point to no longer google myself
Cool !!!  I'm a Surfer. One of the world's most respected Big Wave Surfers.  Gnarly Dude....lol.   Hookset.
Wow...looked mine up...  Says I work in advertising and I have an interest in fishing.  The pic that comes up looks exactly like me.  Oh wait....forget it....is it me....
apparently I play in the NBA (Al Harrington)...  I play Basketball but im not that good.
Apparently I'm a dead entertaining alcoholic and my grandfather was once Prime minister. Dean Martin and Paul Martin.
always google myself (sounds naughty)  Just to check and make sure my personal information has not made it out there..
The very first link that came up on my name.. guess I'm had...  http://www.murphyair.com/complete/WOShea.htm

Apparantly I'm a heart surgeon in Toronto. This fact was hit home recently when when I went to the local TD where I do my banking to transfer funds from one account to another and found I had over 60k in my chequeing account   . The teller had inadvertantly pulled up Mr. Heart Surgeons account by mistake who also happens to bank at TD. Crossed my mind for a nanosecond to transfer a few K into my own savings account... I mean hey, what's a few K to someone with that kinda coin
I found out the hard way that someone with my name AND date of birth declared bankruptcy.  Don't need Google for that.

heres what i got - Currency speculator Joe Lewis, who is actually better known for his financial involvements with football clubs Tottenham Hotspur and Rangers, is now banking on the property development market in Bulgaria, further adding to his multi billion-pound fortune.
Hmm, that said I was a movie director in China. Have had Jet Li star in one or more of the movies.  Second search said I was a doctor in TN.
wow...I'm a funeral director....wait a minute, I am a funeral director.  Guess this game isn't too fun if you have a fairly unique name
I got you all beat. I'm an erotic cartoonist for Hustler magazine.   :thumbsup_anim:
Apparently I'm a boxer out of Kansas City with a zero and fifteen won loss record. No wonder I can't remember anything.
